h (regswaps)\n\nCo-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.6 <noreply@anthropic.com>\n\n* ftKb_SpecialN_800F5EA8 100% match (regswaps)\n\nCo-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.6 <noreply@anthropic.com>\n\n* ft_chara_ftKirby_ftKb_SpecialNNs: decompile ftKb_PrSpecialAirNStart_Coll, ftKb_PrSpecialN_Coll, fn_80105978\n\nCo-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.6 <noreply@anthropic.com>\n\n* ftKb_SpecialN: add dont_inline pragma to prevent inlining of 800F5DE8\n\nMWCC was inlining ftKb_SpecialN_800F5DE8 into ftKb_SpecialNCapture1_Anim\nand ftKb_SpecialAirNCapture_Anim, breaking their 100% matches.\n\nCo-Authored-By: Claude Sonnet 4.6 <noreply@anthropic.com>\n\n* Pop pragma\n\n* Remove pragma usage\n\n* ftKb_SpecialN: wrap dont_inline pragma with push/pop\n\nPrevents the pragma from leaking into subsequent functions,\nwhich broke ftKb_SpecialAirNCapture_Anim (100% → 0%).\n\nCo-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.6 (1M context) <noreply@anthropic.com>\n\n* ftKb_SpecialN: remove leftover dont_inline pragma\n\nCo-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.6 (1M context) <noreply@anthropic.com>\n\n* ftKb_SpecialN: use dont_inline on/off instead of static wrapper\n\nThe static inline wrapper approach still broke\nftKb_SpecialAirNCapture_Anim. Use scoped pragma instead.\n\nCo-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.6 (1M context) <noreply@anthropic.com>\n\n* ftKb_SpecialN: extend dont_inline scope to cover wrapper functions\n\nMove dont_inline off to after ftKb_SpecialAirNCapture_Anim so the\nwrapper functions don't auto-inline their now-visible callees.\n\nCo-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.6 (1M context) <noreply@anthropic.com>\n\n* ftKb_SpecialN: narrow dont_inline to only the two pragma regions\n\nScope dont_inline on/off tightly around ftKb_SpecialN_800F5DE8\nand separately around the two wrapper functions, to avoid\naffecting the ~30 functions in between.\n\nCo-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.6 (1M context) <noreply@anthropic.com>\n\n---------\n\nCo-authored-by: Claude Opus 4.6 <noreply@anthropic.com>\nCo-authored-by: Robin Avery <robin@ribbanya.dev>